    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1861-12-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1861-12-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="247" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d247">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Dayton</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No 95.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic"> Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1861-12-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 28, 1861. SIR: * * * * * * *
                                *</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>You have rightly conjectured that the subject of our relations with Great
                            Britain, as affected by recent events, at present engages the chief
                            attention of the government, so far as foreign affairs are
                            concerned.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William L. Dayton</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
